ciscoItpDsmrUcpMIB.name: ciscoItpDsmrUcpMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoItpDsmrUcpMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems, Inc Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-ss7@cisco.com
ciscoItpDsmrUcpMIB.description: The MIB for providing information about Distributed Short Message Routing delivery using Universal Computer Protocol. Acronyms and Terms: DSMR Distributed Short Message Routing SMPP Short Message Peer-to-Peer (protocol) SMD-PP Short Message Delivery Point to Point. SMS Short Message Service UCP Universal Computer Protocol. WRR Weighted Round Robin. A variation of the round robin algorithm that uses server weights to allow uneven distribution of traffic among a set of available servers. ********************************************

CdsmrUcpInactivityTimer.name: CdsmrUcpInactivityTimer
CdsmrUcpInactivityTimer.description: This textual convention defines the allowed values used to define Inactivity timer used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that an object has not been set to value and that the default value is to be used.

CdsmrUcpResponseTimer.name: CdsmrUcpResponseTimer
CdsmrUcpResponseTimer.description: This textual convention defines the allowed values used to define response timer ,in milliseconds, used by Universal Computer Protocol. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that an object has not been set to value and that the default value is to be used.

CdsmrUcpSendWindow.name: CdsmrUcpSendWindow
CdsmrUcpSendWindow.description: This textual convention defines the allowed values used to define send window used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that an object has not been set to value and that the default value is to be used.

CdsmrUcpSessionInitTimer.name: CdsmrUcpSessionInitTimer
CdsmrUcpSessionInitTimer.description: This textual convention defines the allowed values used to define session initiation timer used to create Universal Computer Protocol. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that an object has not been set to value and that the default value is to be used.

cdsmrUcpSessionStateNotifEnabled.name: cdsmrUcpSessionStateNotifEnabled
cdsmrUcpSessionStateNotifEnabled.description: A control to enable or disable notifications as follows: 'true' Indicates that the ciscoItpDsmrUcpSessionState notification should be generated.. 'false' Indicates that ciscoItpDsmrUcpSessionState notification generation is disabled.

cdsmrUcpProfileTable.name: cdsmrUcpProfileTable
cdsmrUcpProfileTable.description: A table that is used to monitor specific information used to configure universal computer protocol profile. Entries are added to this table via cdsmrUcpProfileRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatus convention.

cdsmrUcpProfileTableEntry.name: cdsmrUcpProfileTableEntry
cdsmrUcpProfileTableEntry.description: Each entry defines parameter that can be used to default values for sessions.

cdsmrUcpProfileName.name: cdsmrUcpProfileName
cdsmrUcpProfileName.description: A name used to define a collection of parameters for short message peer-to-peer protocol.

cdsmrUcpProfileInactivityTimer.name: cdsmrUcpProfileInactivityTimer
cdsmrUcpProfileInactivityTimer.description: This object specifies the duration of the inactivity timer used by Universal Computer Protocol. It indicates the maximum time lapse allowed between transactions before destination is considered inactive.

cdsmrUcpProfileResponseTimer.name: cdsmrUcpProfileResponseTimer
cdsmrUcpProfileResponseTimer.description: This object specifies the duration of the response timer used by Universal Computer Protocol. It indicates the amount of time to wait before retransmitting packet.

cdsmrUcpProfileSendWindow.name: cdsmrUcpProfileSendWindow
cdsmrUcpProfileSendWindow.description: This object specifies the Send Window size to be used by Universal Computer Protocol.

cdsmrUcpProfileSessionInitTimer.name: cdsmrUcpProfileSessionInitTimer
cdsmrUcpProfileSessionInitTimer.description: This object specifies the duration of the session initiation timer used to create Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. It specifies the maximum amount of time to wait for the session Bind to be received.

cdsmrUcpProfileRowStatus.name: cdsmrUcpProfileRowStatus
cdsmrUcpProfileRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cdsmrUcpProfileTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cdsmrUcpSessionTable.name: cdsmrUcpSessionTable
cdsmrUcpSessionTable.description: A table that is used to collection information on universal computer protocol sessions. Entries are added to this table via cdsmrUcpSessionRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatus convention.

cdsmrUcpSessionTableEntry.name: cdsmrUcpSessionTableEntry
cdsmrUcpSessionTableEntry.description: Each entry defines parameter and state information on universal computer protocol sessions.

cdsmrUcpSessionLocalPortNumber.name: cdsmrUcpSessionLocalPortNumber
cdsmrUcpSessionLocalPortNumber.description: Local port number used to establish Ucp Session.

cdsmrUcpSessionLocalIpAddrType.name: cdsmrUcpSessionLocalIpAddrType
cdsmrUcpSessionLocalIpAddrType.description: This object contains the type of the local IP address used to create an session.

cdsmrUcpSessionLocalIpAddress.name: cdsmrUcpSessionLocalIpAddress
cdsmrUcpSessionLocalIpAddress.description: This object contains the local IP address used to create the session with the partner of this session.

cdsmrUcpSessionDynamicDest.name: cdsmrUcpSessionDynamicDest
cdsmrUcpSessionDynamicDest.description: Indicates whether dynamic destinations are allowed as follows. 'true' - dynamic destination are allowed. 'false' - dynamic destinations are not allowed.

cdsmrUcpSessionRowStatus.name: cdsmrUcpSessionRowStatus
cdsmrUcpSessionRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cdsmrUcpSessionTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cdsmrUcpDestTable.name: cdsmrUcpDestTable
cdsmrUcpDestTable.description: A table that is used to define a collection of information on used to universal computer protocol destinations. Entries are added to this table via cdsmrUcpDestRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatus convention.

cdsmrUcpDestTableEntry.name: cdsmrUcpDestTableEntry
cdsmrUcpDestTableEntry.description: Each entry defines parameter and state information on short message peer-to-peer protocol destinations.

cdsmrUcpDestName.name: cdsmrUcpDestName
cdsmrUcpDestName.description: A name used to uniquely identify a destination using short message peer-to-peer protocol.

cdsmrUcpDestInactivityTimer.name: cdsmrUcpDestInactivityTimer
cdsmrUcpDestInactivityTimer.description: This object defines the allowed values used to define inactivity timer used by Universal Computer Protocol. Indicates the maximum time lapse allowed between transactions before destination is considered inactive.

cdsmrUcpDestResponseTimer.name: cdsmrUcpDestResponseTimer
cdsmrUcpDestResponseTimer.description: This object specifies the duration of the response timer used by Universal Computer Protocol. It indicates the amount of time to wait before retransmitting packet.

cdsmrUcpDestSendWindow.name: cdsmrUcpDestSendWindow
cdsmrUcpDestSendWindow.description: This object specifies the Send Window size to be used by Universal Computer Protocol.

cdsmrUcpDestSessionInitTimer.name: cdsmrUcpDestSessionInitTimer
cdsmrUcpDestSessionInitTimer.description: This object specifies the duration of the session initiation timer used to create Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. It specifies the maximum amount of time to wait for the session Bind to be received.

cdsmrUcpDestRemotePortNumber.name: cdsmrUcpDestRemotePortNumber
cdsmrUcpDestRemotePortNumber.description: Remote port number used to establish short message peer-to-peer protocol session.

cdsmrUcpDestRemoteIpAddrType.name: cdsmrUcpDestRemoteIpAddrType
cdsmrUcpDestRemoteIpAddrType.description: This object contains the type of the remote IP address used to create an session.

cdsmrUcpDestRemoteIpAddress.name: cdsmrUcpDestRemoteIpAddress
cdsmrUcpDestRemoteIpAddress.description: This object contains the remote IP address used to create the session.

cdsmrUcpDestProfileName.name: cdsmrUcpDestProfileName
cdsmrUcpDestProfileName.description: Specifies Profile from cdsmrUcpProfileTable table to define common default parameters for session.

cdsmrUcpDestState.name: cdsmrUcpDestState
cdsmrUcpDestState.description: Current state of destination. 'active' - Destination is available. 'inactive' - Destination is unvailable. 'open' - Device is listening on port for destination to establish connection.

cdsmrUcpDestSentRequests.name: cdsmrUcpDestSentRequests
cdsmrUcpDestSentRequests.description: Number of SMS requests sent to destination.

cdsmrUcpDestRcvdRequests.name: cdsmrUcpDestRcvdRequests
cdsmrUcpDestRcvdRequests.description: Number of SMS requests received from destination.

cdsmrUcpDestSentResponses.name: cdsmrUcpDestSentResponses
cdsmrUcpDestSentResponses.description: Number of SMS responses sent to destination.

cdsmrUcpDestRcvdResponses.name: cdsmrUcpDestRcvdResponses
cdsmrUcpDestRcvdResponses.description: Number of SMS responses received from destination.

cdsmrUcpDestRowStatus.name: cdsmrUcpDestRowStatus
cdsmrUcpDestRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cdsmrUcpDestTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

ciscoItpDsmrUcpSessionState.name: ciscoItpDsmrUcpSessionState
ciscoItpDsmrUcpSessionState.description: This notification is generated whenever SMPP destination changes state. This notification provides information on the availablity of the destination to receive and process packets using the UCP protocol.

ciscoItpDsmrUcpMIBCompliance.name: ciscoItpDsmrUcpMIBCompliance
ciscoItpDsmrUcpMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco CISCO-ITP-MLR-MIB

ciscoItpDsmrUcpGroup.name: ciscoItpDsmrUcpGroup
ciscoItpDsmrUcpGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information used to configure UCP profile and notifications.

ciscoItpDsmrUcpNotificationsGroup.name: ciscoItpDsmrUcpNotificationsGroup
ciscoItpDsmrUcpNotificationsGroup.description: DSMR Universal Computer Protocol notification objects.
